                    <h2 class="section-title h4 mb-3">Badges</h2>
                    <p>CAIS is an ACM conference and thus uses ACM's official AE badges. Authors can apply for, and be awarded, one of three combinations for their artifacts and associated papers:</p>

                    <table style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                        <tr>
                            <td  style="white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: middle; min-width: 210px;">
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_available_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Available badge">
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_functional_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Functional badge">
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_reproduced_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Reproduced badge">
                            </td>
                            <td>
                                For the vast majority of software artifacts, and for hardware artifacts whenever possible.
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_available_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Available badge">
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_functional_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Functional badge">
                            </td>
                            <td>
                                For data sets, as well as artifacts that require custom environments authors can’t give access to.
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_functional_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Functional badge">
                                <img src="/assets/images/badges_acm_reproduced_1.1.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; object-fit: cover;" alt="ACM Reproduced badge">
                            </td>
                            <td>
                                For software and hardware artifacts that the authors cannot make public.
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>

                    <p>Artifacts submitted for the first target may be awarded one of the other two if availability or reproducibility evaluations fail, respectively. Authors cannot apply for other combinations of badges as these make little sense, such as "an artifact that is not public, does not appear functional, but outputs the right numbers".</p>

                    <p>Authors and AEC reviewers are encouraged to read the following <a href="https://sysartifacts.github.io/cais2026/badges" target="_blank" rel="noopener">badge awarding guidelines</a>.</p>
                </section>
                
